abstract: >-
  LHC (Long-Horizon Coherence) is a decontaminated, audit-validated open
  benchmark that measures and discriminates 8B-class language models on
  three long-horizon failure modes — state recall, decision consistency,
  and workflow resumption — across a 4-mode gap-condition ablation.
  Released alongside the honest training record of Ember v0.1.5, a
  Qwen3-8B fine-tune that did not measurably beat its base under
  matched local inference.
